GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 1
SENATE BILL 649
Short Title: Restore Master's Pay for Teachers & ISP. (Public)
Sponsors: Senator Mohammed (Primary Sponsor).
Referred to: Rules and Operations of the Senate
March 26, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO REINSTATE EDUCATION-BASED SALARY SUPPLEMENTS FOR
3 TEACHERS AND INSTRUCTIONAL SUPPORT PERSONNEL.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. G.S. 115C-302.10 is repealed.
6 SECTION 2. Notwithstanding any other provision of law, for the 2025-2026 fiscal
7 year, State Board of Education policy TCP-A-006, as it was in effect on June 30, 2013, shall be
8 used to determine (i) whether teachers and instructional support personnel are paid on the "M"
9 salary schedule and (ii) whether they receive a salary supplement for academic preparation at the
10 six-year or doctoral degree level.
11 SECTION 3. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of
12 Public Instruction the sum of eight million dollars ($8,000,000) in recurring funds for the
13 2025-2026 fiscal year to reinstate education-based salary supplements for teachers and
14 instructional support personnel in accordance with this act.
15 SECTION 4. This act becomes effective July 1, 2025.
*S649-v-1*

